A DFT-based approach for the analysis of material damage and fatigue life using a nonlocal strain gradient model - ScienceDirect
International Journal of Mechanical Sciences
Volume 162, 1 January 2020, 105432
A DFT-based approach for the analysis of material damage and fatigue life using a nonlocal strain gradient model
Author links open overlay panel
YanpingZhangab ZhiyuanZhangc ChuanmingChenb
https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ijmecsci.2019.105432 Get rights and content
Highlights
•
A DFT-based approach is proposed for damage analysis.
•
Nonlocal strain gradient theory is introduced for the analysis of micro scale.
•
The fatigue life model is established based on the DFT method.
•
The model is validated through comparison with experimental data.
Abstract
In this work, a damage mechanics model is proposed based on the density functional theory (DFT) and the nonlocal strain gradient theory. The model takes into account the microstructural effects by introducing the nonlocal strain gradient theory, which considers the size effect of materials at different scales. The DFT method is used to calculate the energy of crystal lattice, and the energy change is used to reflect the damage evolution. The fatigue life prediction model is established based on the DFT method. The model is validated through comparison with experimental data. The results show that the model can effectively reflect the damage evolution and fatigue life of materials under low cycle fatigue (LCF) loading. The model with the nonlocal strain gradient theory presents better results than the conventional DFT-based model without considering the size effect. Moreover, the model can capture the effects of microstructural parameters, and the predicted fatigue life decreases with the increase of the nonlocal parameter and the gradient parameter. The model is expected to be used for the prediction of the fatigue life of materials at the micro scale.
